## Docker Commands to cretae a Mongo database server and access it with Mongo Express ##

* First we have to check the docker network *
   
   docker network ls                                                            <It will list all network in docker>
   docker network create mongo-network                                          <will have to create a network>

* To pull the image and run the mongo DB container *
  
  docker run -d \
> -p 27017:27017 \
> --name mongo \
> --network mongo-network \
> -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME=admin \
> -e MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD=qwerty \
> mongo


* To pull theimage and run the mongo-express *                                  <TO access the GUI of mongodb>

  docker run -d \
> -p 8081:8081 \
> --name mongo-express \
> --network mongo-network \
> -e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINUSERNAME=admin \
> -e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_ADMINPASSWORD=qwerty \
> -e ME_CONFIG_MONGODB_SERVER=mongo \
> mongo-express

Use mongo-express to access the GUI of mongo database 